---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Taiwan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/taiwan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Japan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/japan' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Malaysia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/malaysia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'taiwanFit', header: 'Taiwan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$380-530/mo', taiwanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$450-620/mo', taiwanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$340-480/mo', taiwanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$320-460/mo', taiwanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Taiwan NHI', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'NT$1,400-2,000', taiwanFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$340-530', annual: '$4,080-6,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$480-700', annual: '$5,760-8,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$640-950', annual: '$7,680-11,400' },
  { category: 'Taiwan NHI (Resident)', monthly: 'NT$1,400-2,000', annual: 'NT$16,800-24,000' },
  { category: 'Taiwan Private Supplement', monthly: 'NT$2,000-5,000', annual: 'NT$24,000-60,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Taiwan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Taiwan. NHI healthcare system, Taipei hospitals, Gold Card visa, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Taiwan"
  subheadline="Taiwan offers world-class healthcare at affordable costs, modern infrastructure, and welcoming culture—with an excellent national health insurance system."
  heroImage="/images/countries/taiwan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Taiwan</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan consistently surprises retirees with its excellent healthcare, safety, modern infrastructure, and affordable cost of living. The National Health Insurance (NHI) system is renowned globally, and quality of life is high in this tech-savvy, friendly nation.
  </p>

  <p>
    Taipei offers everything a major city provides, with excellent MRT and hospitals. Kaohsiung in the south has warmer weather and lower costs. Taichung is centrally located with good climate. East coast cities like Hualien offer dramatic scenery and slower pace.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> World-class; NHI ranked among best globally</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Mandarin; English limited outside major areas</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> NT$50,000-80,000/month ($1,600-2,600)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Subtropical; hot humid summers, mild winters</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Very safe; one of Asia's safest places</li>
      <li><strong>Technology:</strong> Highly developed; convenience stores everywhere</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Taiwan's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan's National Health Insurance (NHI) is often cited as one of the world's best healthcare systems. It covers 99.9% of the population, provides comprehensive coverage, and keeps costs remarkably low. Expats with ARC (residence) can enroll after 6 months.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare quality is excellent. Taipei's medical centers (Taipei Veterans General, National Taiwan University Hospital) rival any in the world. Wait times are minimal. A specialist visit costs under $10 with NHI. The system is efficient and patient-friendly.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Language Barrier</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      While Taiwan is welcoming, Mandarin Chinese is essential for daily life and healthcare outside major hospitals. Some Taipei hospitals have international departments with English support. Learning basic Mandarin significantly improves the healthcare experience.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan has been improving options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Taiwan Gold Card</h3>
  <p>
    For skilled professionals, including retirees with significant expertise or income. Provides 1-3 year residency with open work permit. After 6 months with ARC, can join NHI.
  </p>

  <h3>Resident Visa (Financial Independence)</h3>
  <p>
    Available to those with Taiwan bank deposits of NT$5 million+ (~$160,000) or proof of pension income. Requires comprehensive health insurance initially.
  </p>

  <h3>Visitor Visa Extensions</h3>
  <p>
    Many countries get 90-day visa-free entry. Extensions possible but limited. Long-term visitors need to exit and re-enter. No NHI access on visitor status.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements vary by status:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Resident visa:</strong> Comprehensive insurance required for application</li>
    <li><strong>Gold Card:</strong> NHI access after 6 months with ARC</li>
    <li><strong>Visitors:</strong> No NHI access; need travel/international insurance</li>
    <li><strong>NHI enrollment:</strong> After 6 months legal residency</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Taiwan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Use international insurance for the initial 6 months before NHI eligibility. Once enrolled in NHI, it covers most care affordably. Keep international insurance for travel, evacuation, and home country coverage. NHI is remarkably cost-effective.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Taiwan, these providers offer strong coverage during the pre-NHI period and beyond:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Taiwan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Taiwan network, direct billing at major hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), strong Asian coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive pricing for Asia-Pacific</li>
    <li><strong>Taiwan NHI:</strong> Once eligible, exceptional value</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Taiwan.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Taiwan healthcare costs are remarkably affordable once you have NHI:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Get NHI quickly:</strong> Establish residency and qualify after 6 months</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> During initial period, $5,000+ deductible saves substantially</li>
    <li><strong>Taiwan exclusion:</strong> Once on NHI, exclude Taiwan from international policy</li>
    <li><strong>Direct pay:</strong> Taiwan healthcare is so cheap, paying cash for minor issues is feasible</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Gold Card Holder, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Former tech executive with Gold Card. Arriving in Taipei.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for first 6 months. After ARC issued, enroll in NHI. Keep Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~$450/month. After NHI: ~NT$1,600/month NHI + reduced Cigna ~$250/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring to Kaohsiung. NT$6M (~$190K) in Taiwan bank. Resident visa.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global during 6-month waiting period. NHI after. BUPA for UK coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~$1,100/month combined. After NHI: ~$600/month (BUPA reduced + minimal NHI).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Japanese Heritage, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Japanese citizen with Taiwan ancestry connection. Long-term residence.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Qualify for residency through ancestry. NHI access after 6 months. Allianz for Japan visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> NHI ~NT$1,800/month + Allianz ~$300/month. Excellent combined coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Taiwan's healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Exceptional. Taiwan's NHI is often ranked #1 or #2 globally for efficiency. Wait times are minimal—you can often see a specialist same-day. Costs are incredibly low. A doctor visit is ~$5, a hospital night ~$30-50 with NHI. Quality matches developed Western countries.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English widely spoken?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Less than you might expect. Young people in Taipei often speak some English, but proficiency varies. Healthcare providers in international departments speak English; neighborhood clinics usually don't. Learning basic Mandarin is strongly recommended for daily life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is the Gold Card program?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Taiwan's Gold Card is an employment gold card combining residence, work permit, and re-entry permit. It's available to foreign professionals in 8 fields, including those with high salaries or special expertise. Some retirees with notable careers qualify. It provides a fast track to residence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the political situation?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Taiwan's cross-strait relationship with China is complex. Day-to-day life is completely normal and safe. Taiwan is a vibrant democracy. Many long-term expats live there without concern. However, the geopolitical situation is worth understanding before committing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Taiwan.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Taiwan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
